<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1158,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,412,1758,1784]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Biology.</emphasis>
This species inhabits cloud forests and coffee plantations located at altitudes from 
<quantity box="[333,534,1799,1825]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="1900.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="1800.0">1800 to 2000 m</quantity>
. Months of collection: September (1), November (8), December (53). The adults of this species fly during late autumn, which is notable because other Central American species are usually active during spring and summer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
